third_party/evi/ — libevi_crypto redistribution (Pattern C, static-only)
=========================================================================

This tree ships prebuilt static archives + C/C++ headers alongside the Go
source so that `go get github.com/CryptoLabInc/envector-go-sdk` plus
`-tags libevi` can produce a self-contained single Go binary via cgo
without any external C++ toolchain on the consumer side.

Only static archives ship. Shared variants (.so/.dylib/.dll + MinGW import
libs) are intentionally NOT redistributed — the SDK's contract is a single
statically-linked binary, and shared libraries would just add weight and a
runtime dependency.

Four archives are shipped per platform:

  libevi_c_api.a    Thin C ABI wrapper (`extern "C"` entry points such as
                    `evi_context_create`, `evi_encryptor_create`, ...).
                    This is what cgo links against directly.
  libevi_crypto.a   Underlying C++ implementation that libevi_c_api calls
                    into. Links with unresolved `deb::*` / `_alea_*`
                    references that the two dependency archives below
                    resolve. NONE-mode seal path only; OpenSSL-using
                    SealInfo/AES-KEK code paths live in `.o` members that
                    the static linker does not pull in when the SDK stays
                    on `seal_mode=NONE` (verified on darwin_arm64: final
                    binary's only dynamic deps are libc++ + libSystem).
  libdeb.a          CPM-sourced dependency (CryptoLabInc/deb). Provides
                    the CKKS numeric layer (`deb::*` C++ symbols) that
                    libevi_crypto invokes. Not a transitive include of
                    libevi_crypto because CMake's `target_link_libraries`
                    only propagates link order, not archive contents.
  libalea.a         Sub-library of deb, built alongside it via
                    `DEB_INSTALL_ALEA=ON`. Provides the RNG primitives
                    (`_alea_*` C symbols) that libdeb uses.

The three-archive bundle (libevi_crypto + libdeb + libalea) mirrors the
`evi/lib/` layout that pyenvector ships in its wheel; we take the same
approach for the same reason.

